  <refsection>
    <title>Particular cases</title>
    <para>
There is no Scilab equivalent function for Matlab box but it can be easyly replaced by Scilab equivalent instructions.
</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <informaltable border="1" pgwide="1">
      <tr>
        <td align="center">
          <emphasis role="bold">Matlab</emphasis>
        </td>
        <td align="center">
          <emphasis role="bold">Scilab</emphasis>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
box on
box off
box
box(h,'on')
box(h,'off')
box(h)
]]></programlisting>
        </td>
        <td>
          <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
a = gca();
a.box = "on";
a.box = "off";
if a.box=="on" then a.box="off";else a.box="on";end;
h.box = "on";
h.box = "off";
if h.box=="on" then h.box="off";else h.box="on";end;
]]></programlisting>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </informaltable>
  </refsection>
